<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Centered Ruffle Window</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex; /* Makes the body a flex container */
            flex-direction: column; /* Stacks children vertically */
            justify-content: center; /* Centers content vertically */
            align-items: center; /* Centers content horizontally */
            min-height: 100vh; /* Ensures the body takes full viewport height */
            margin: 0; /* Remove default body margin */
            background-color: #f0f0f0; /* Light gray background */
        }

        .ruffle-container {
            width: 80%; /* Adjust as needed */
            max-width: 600px; /* Optional: Sets a maximum width */
            background-color: white;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            text-align: center; /* Centers the header and text inside the container */
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        /* Styling for the Ruffle player itself (within the container) */
        #ruffle-player {
            width: 100%;
            height: 400px; /* Adjust as needed for your Flash content */
            background-color: black;
            margin-top: 15px; /* Adds space between header and Ruffle player */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="ruffle-container">
        <h1>Pac-Xon: Hero Strikes Back!</h1>
        <div id="ruffle-player">
            <!-- Ruffle Flash player will be embedded here via JavaScript -->
        </div>
        <p> Controls: Arrow Keys to Move.</p>
    <p>Ah, good ol' Pac-Xon. This was nothing like I had ever seen up to this point. Though now I know it's basically a clone of 

the arcade game Qix, the unique abilities and Pac-Man themeing made me come back to this one over and over. I remember this used 

to be on a lot of Flash Game websites that hosted other Namco arcade clones, one of them being this Galaga or Galaxian clone with 

a weird name... Anyone remember that one?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Ruffle JS script to embed Flash content -->
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/@ruffle-rs/ruffle"></script>
    <script>
        window.RufflePlayer = window.RufflePlayer || {};
        window.addEventListener("load", (event) => {
            const ruffle = window.RufflePlayer.newest();
            const player = ruffle.createPlayer();
            const container = document.getElementById("ruffle-player");
            container.appendChild(player);
            player.load({
                url: "../ruffle-example/flashfiles/327718_pacxon.swf", // Replace with your .swf file path
                backgroundColor: "#000",
            });
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
